In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 5 through September 7, 2014, as National Days of Prayer and Remembrance in honor of the victims of the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks. The proclamation encourages the people of the United States to remember the tragedy through prayer, contemplation, memorial services, visiting memorials, ringing bells, candlelight vigils, and other appropriate activities. The President also invites people around the world to participate in this commemoration. The article emphasizes the importance of love, compassion, and sacrifice, and highlights the resilience and strength of the American people in the face of terror.